## 🔑 Key Concepts

| Term | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Network Address** | First address in a subnet (all host bits = 0) — identifies the subnet, not assignable |
| **Broadcast Address** | Last address in a subnet (all host bits = 1) — sends to all hosts in subnet, not assignable |
| **Usable Host Addresses** | Everything between network & broadcast — assignable to devices |
| **Subnet Mask** | 32-bit number; ANDed with IP to split network vs host portion |
| **CIDR** | `/n` notation — replaced classful system; `n` = number of network bits |

