## 📐 Worked Example 1 — /24 → /27 (need ≥25 hosts/subnet)

1. **Host requirement:** need ≥25 → 2⁵−2 = 30 ✅ → need **5 host bits**
2. **Borrow:** /24 has 8 host bits → borrow 8−5 = **3 bits** → new CIDR = **/27**, mask = `255.255.255.224`
3. **Subnets created:** 2³ = 8
4. **Magic number:** 256−224 = 32

| Subnet # | Network | Broadcast | Usable Hosts |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | 192.168.1.0 | 192.168.1.31 | .1–.30 |
| 1 | 192.168.1.32 | 192.168.1.63 | .33–.62 |
| 2 | 192.168.1.64 | 192.168.1.95 | .65–.94 |
| 3 | 192.168.1.96 | 192.168.1.127 | .97–.126 |
| 4 | 192.168.1.128 | 192.168.1.159 | .129–.158 |
| 5 | 192.168.1.160 | 192.168.1.191 | .161–.190 |
| 6 | 192.168.1.192 | 192.168.1.223 | .193–.222 |
| 7 | 192.168.1.224 | 192.168.1.255 | .225–.254 |

