## 📝 Chapter Summary

- Classful addressing (A/B/C) wasted addresses and created huge broadcast domains
- Subnetting borrows host bits to create smaller, manageable subnets
- CIDR replaced fixed classes with flexible `/n` prefix notation
- Two formulas drive all subnetting: **2ⁿ subnets** and **2^(H−n) − 2 usable hosts**
- The "magic number" (256 − mask octet value) gives quick subnet range increments
- Subnetting isn't limited to the last octet — larger blocks (/16, /8) subnet in earlier octets
- Good segmentation = smaller broadcast domains + easier firewalling + cleaner admin

